<div class=accordion id=featuresaccordion>
  <div class="accordion-group"> 
    <h3 class=accordion-heading data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#featuresaccordion" data-target="#collapseOne">
      Scratch Pad
    </h3>
    <div class="collapse" id=collapseOne>
      <div class="accordion-inner">
        <h4>1. Notes</h4>
        <p>Type your notes in the highlighted field. Press enter to commit the notes onto the scratch pad. To make this more like a classroom or exam situation, we don't allow students to edit the notes once they have entered them.</p>
        <h4>2. Operations</h4>
        <p>To allow you to add, subtract or multiply like you do in your notes in class, we have created online forms for you. To access these forms either click on the corresponding button on the top left of the notepad or write in the operation in the notes field followed by Shift-Enter (For example, to multiply 123 and 12, write 123*12 followed by Shift-Enter).</p>
        <h4>3. Scratch Work</h4>
        <p>You can also draw on the pad by clicking and dragging.</p>
        <h4>4. Next or Provious Page</h4>
        <p>To go to the next page, click on the arrow to the right of the pad. To go to the previous page, click on the arrow to the left of the page. Remember, you can only add new notes onto the last page.</p>
        <h4>5. Comments</h4>
        <p>You can add comments onto currently non-active pages by double clicking in the margin on the line you wish to comment on. Click on the notepad to save the comment. To access a comment for a particular line, click on the icon in the margin for that particular line.</p>
        <br style="clear:both;">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
